The claim of the U: S. Army seizing a computer server from Scytl to prove election fraud was found to be baseless and false.
Scytl: the election software company, does not have a server in Frankfurt, Germany, as claimed in the false information.
The U: S. Army did not conduct any raid or seizure on Scytl, debunking the claim made by Rep. Louie Gohmert.
The false claim was spread by Rep: Louie Gohmert, as well as conservative news outlets Newsmax and One America News, despite the lack of evidence or factual basis.
